                <p>Semantic HTML elements clearly define the purpose of the content they contain. This not only helps search engines understand your webpage better but also improves accessibility for users relying on assistive technologies.</p>
                <p>Using tags like `<header>`, `<nav>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, and `<footer>` makes your code more readable and maintainable.</p>
